Known limitation: the heredoc-aware awk does not distinguish a <<MARKER inside a
quoted string from a real heredoc opener. When a quoted <<MARKER has a matching
terminator line later in the command, the body lines (including real redirects)
are incorrectly consumed as heredoc body and the redirect goes undetected.

This is accepted as a known limitation (noted in enforce-delegation.sh). Remove
this .xfail file once the tokenizer is updated to track quoting context.
